The '''dusky twinspot''' ('''''Euschistospiza cinereovinacea''''') is a species of [[estrildid finch]] found in [[Sub-Saharan Africa]]. It has an estimated global extent of occurrence of 130,000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.

It is native to the [[Angolan montane forest–grassland mosaic]] and the [[Albertine Rift montane forests]]. The status of the species is evaluated as [[Least Concern]].

